  "text": "Premature infants are at significant risk for AKI because of high rates of infection and exposure to nephrotoxic medications (6); however, the exact incidence of AKI in this population is unknown. The incidence of neonatal AKI, estimated at 8 -24% of the general neonatal population, is probably an under-estimate as they only describe those with nonoliguric renal failure and use either high levels of SCr or dialysis provision to define AKI [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] .",
